Team





Partners



Tom SandellChairman & Chief Executive Officer



 


Tom founded Sandell Asset Management in January 1998 and is the Chairman and CEO
			He has been involved in the securities industry since May 1986. Tom joined Bear Stearns in 1989 to establish the proprietary international risk arbitrage operation. When he left in 1997 he was a Senior Managing Director and co-head of the Risk Arbitrage department.  Previously, Tom worked as a securities analyst for Atlantic Finance in Paris from May 1986 to May 1987 and subsequently was head of equity research at Group Delphi in Paris.  He received a BS in International Business Administration and Economics from Uppsala University (Sweden) and an MBA in Finance from Columbia Business School.

He is a founding Board Member and the current Chairman of The New Leader’s Group of the Institute of International Education, the administrator of the US Government’s Fulbright Program.  He is also a Trustee of Friends of ARK (Absolute Return for Kids). Tom was born and raised in Sweden and resides in London.
			






Raj DavéSenior Managing Director & Partner



 


			
			Raj Davé is Head of Credit Opportunities and a Senior Managing Director / Portfolio Manager at Sandell Asset Management Corp.  Raj joined the investment team in 2013. Prior to Sandell, Raj was a Director at Citigroup focused on Distressed & High Yield Debt and a Credit Opportunities Portfolio Manager at Diamond Notch Asset Management. Between 2002 - 2008, Raj was Portfolio Manager at Morgan Stanley on the Proprietary Credit trading desk and also at Commerzbank Capital Corp.  He also worked in Investment Banking & Leverage Finance at UBS and Credit Suisse, respectively from 1997 - 2002. Raj holds an MBA from Rollins College and resides in New York City.
			






Felix LoSenior Managing Director & Partner



 


			
			Felix Lo is a Senior Managing Director and Partner with a primary focus on merger arbitrage and international equity special situations. Felix re-joined the investment team at Sandell Asset Management Corp in 2013. Felix previously worked at Sandell as an Analyst from 2006 to 2009, before co-founding Granite Fund Advisors in 2010, a Hong Kong based long /short equity hedge fund, where he was responsible for the global event driven strategy. From 2004 to 2006, Felix worked as an Analyst at Evercore Partners. Felix graduated magna cum laude in 2004 with a B.S. in Economics from The Wharton School, and a B.S.E in Computer Science Engineering from the School of Engineering and Applied Science at the University of Pennsylvania.
			






Rick  EcklordSenior Managing Director & Partner



 


			
			Rick Ecklord is a Senior Managing Director and Partner, with primary responsibility for trading and technology. Rick joined Sandell Asset Management Corp. in 2001. From 2000 to 2001, Rick worked for Spear, Leeds & Kellogg / Goldman Sachs, Inc. as a trader. He worked for Renata Trading LLC, as an options trader in 2000. From 1998 to 2000, Rick worked for Sakura Dellshar, Inc. as a trader. He worked for McNamara Trading Inc., as a trader in 1996 to 1998 and with AIG Trading Group as an assistant trader in 1996. Rick graduated from The Citadel, The Military College of South Carolina in 1995.
			










